reviews.review_text: what a show! I was there, 31 years ago, 8/4/74, Philly Civic Center - incredible show - the Dead were touring with the infamous "wall of sound" pa system, a huge setup that usually took half of the 1st set to get right, so by the 4th or 5th tune the vocals got clearer & the overall sound felt right.  That was the most intricate pa that any band had ever used, but it filled the hall like nothing you ever heard before.  The show was one of those extra long ones that showcased the band's amazingly varied repertoire.  The new tunes from "Mars Hotel" were very well done, & the "Weather Report Suite" was, well, SWEET.  Jerry Moore was well known for making great tapes, & I have cassette dubs of the originals.  This, of course, is better.  The transfer is excellent, and considering the original source (UD-120s, in the audience), I consider the sound quality to be as good as can be expected.  Fantastic show, very nicely reproduced.  Brings back great memories......
Peggy-O This is a very slow and sweet version.  I love it!

Why did I enjoy the first over the second? It's recorded by the same Moore. Granted the second night has the far more interesting 'Scarlet' and a hard-chargin 'Around.'

Maybe it's for the that aching minimalist "Peggy." The cohesive 'Jack' that beckoned to be stretched further. Jerry's noodling during 'El Paso.' Those few extra desperate notes of 'Wharf.' 

Regardless, the swirl of sounds collected added up to a more pleasing experience. Recommended!
good aud great 74 show here, classic songs and great setlist for both of em, love the end of the 2nd, us blues is great in 74, overall great show
74' Classic Good, classic show typical of the Wall of Sound Era.  Best tunes for me were the super long Playin' and, of course, the full Weather Report Suite.  Definitely worth a listen...

Dick's Picks 31 On Dick's Picks "Jack Straw" (disc 1) is from August 4, "Scarlet Begonias" (disc 1) is from August 5 and as far as I know "U.S. Blues" (disc 2) is from August 4.

They used a section of "Scarlet Begonias" from August 4 to cover the gap in the board recording of the August 6 version (disc 4).

as if present still!  and grateful. I was all of 13 years when I was at this show.  I remember parts of it as vividly now as anything from that time of my life.  Being a kid - and this being in a the cavernous convention center (where a googleplex of hospitals and medical centers now stands in west philly), I remember standing just off stage to the side and taking in the spectacle, free to roam around, the colors, the everyday-ness of the guys in the band just ... playing ... Playing in the Band, US Blues ... I'm amazed how well you can hear and feel the ambience of the space, almost the physical dimensions of it (being very different and more resonant than a seated concert hall) in this recording.  Grateful for this recording and grateful to have been there and then to be here - and both at the same time, some 40 years plus later.  Besides the fact that I think this is just an awesome show anyway.  Thanks <3
